            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>To Cantria Longina, daughter of Publius, flaminica of Diva Iulia Pia Augusta, and sacerdos of the Great Idaean Mother of the Gods, and of Isis the Queen. This woman gave 50,000 sesterces to the res publica in honour of her priesthoods. This (statue?) was decreed publicly by the decurions.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Cantria Longina held the priesthood of the divine Julia, the daughter of Titus (cf. Gregori and Rosso 2010, 202, who believe this to be Iulia Augusta, the niece of Caligula. There is undoubtedly a relationship between Cantria Longina here and the Cantria Paulla of <ref target="EmpWor000293.xml">EmpWor000293</ref> and <ref target="EmpWor000296.xml">EmpWor000296</ref>. Our Cantria Longina was the wife of M. Pomponius Bassulus (CIL 9.1164), and the mother of the Roman eques M. Pomponius Bassulus Longinianus (for the latter see Granino Cecere 2014).</p> 
            </div>
